Main spheres and concepts:
The preconditions and development of Estonian professional culture. The role of education in the professionalisation of culture. Classical types of culture: theater, music, cinema, literature and fine arts. The merging of boundaries between types of culture. New art culture: multimedia and other high-tech possibilities. Cultural policy of democratic and totalitarian society. Commercialisation of culture. Creative industry.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the course is to introduce Estonian culture development and achievements. The subject expands on development of various culture types and their relationship with different culture paradigms.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  General competences:
Students are aware of different concepts and key achievements of Estonian cultural history. 
Competences:
Is able to analyse the developments and tendencies of different types of culture.Is able to put cultural terms and facts into use.
Is able to analyse the background and operating mechanisms of culture-related phenomena.
